[{"location":"guide/#User-Guide","page":"User Guide","title":"User Guide","text":"This guide explains how to use PyTensorStore.jl to read and write multi-dimensional arrays.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Opening-a-Store","page":"User Guide","title":"Opening a Store","text":"To open a TensorStore, use the PyTensorStore.open function with a configuration dictionary (Spec). This returns a FutureWrapper, and you can use .result() to wait for the store to open.\n\nusing PyTensorStore\n\nspec = Dict(\n    \"driver\" => \"zarr\",\n    \"kvstore\" => \"memory://test_array\",\n    \"dtype\" => \"int32\",\n    \"metadata\" => Dict(\"shape\" => [100, 200]),\n    \"create\" => true\n)\n\nw = PyTensorStore.open(spec).result()","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Basic-Operations","page":"User Guide","title":"Basic Operations","text":"PyTensorStore.jl supports standard Julia 1-based indexing:\n\n# Write data (synchronously via setindex!)\nw[1:10, 1:10] = rand(Int32, 10, 10)\n\n# Read data (returns a FutureWrapper)\nread_future = w[1:5, 1:5].read()\ndata = read_future.result() # Returns a PyArray","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Labeled-Indexing","page":"User Guide","title":"Labeled Indexing","text":"TensorStore supports labeling dimensions, allowing you to index by name:\n\n# Create with labels\nspec[\"schema\"] = Dict(\"domain\" => Dict(\"labels\" => [\"lat\", \"lon\"]))\nw = PyTensorStore.open(spec).result()\n\n# Use keywords for labeled dimensions\nsub_w = w[lat=1:5, lon=10:15]","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Transactions","page":"User Guide","title":"Transactions","text":"Atomic multi-write operations can be performed by using a transaction block. All changes made within the block are committed together when the block finishes.\n\nPyTensorStore.transaction() do txn\n    w_txn = w.with_transaction(txn)\n    w_txn[1, 1] = 42\n    w_txn[2, 2] = 100\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/#Domain-Manipulation","page":"User Guide","title":"Domain Manipulation","text":"You can transform the coordinate system of a TensorStore without moving the underlying data.\n\ntranslate_by(w, offsets...): Shift the coordinate system by a relative amount.\ntranslate_to(w, coords...): Shift the coordinate system so that the origin is at the specified coordinates (1-based Julia coordinates).\nlabel(w, labels...): Assign new labels to the dimensions.\n\nshifted = translate_by(w, 10, 20)\n@assert axes(shifted) == (11:110, 21:220)","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#Public-API","page":"API Reference","title":"Public API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#Python-Module-Wrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"Python Module Wrapper","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.ChunkLayoutWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.ChunkLayoutWrapper","text":"ChunkLayoutWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.ChunkLayout object. Describes how data is chunked on disk.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.FutureWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.FutureWrapper","text":"FutureWrapper{Result}(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.Future object. Result is the Julia type that the future will resolve to when .result() is called.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.IndexDomainWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.IndexDomainWrapper","text":"IndexDomainWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.IndexDomain object. Represents the coordinate system and labels of a TensorStore.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.SchemaWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.SchemaWrapper","text":"SchemaWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.Schema object. Describes the data type, domain, and layout of a TensorStore.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.SpecWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.SpecWrapper","text":"SpecWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.Spec object. Represents a serializable specification of a TensorStore.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.TensorStoreWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.TensorStoreWrapper","text":"TensorStoreWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.TensorStore object. Implements much of the Julia AbstractArray interface.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.TransactionWrapper","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.TransactionWrapper","text":"TransactionWrapper(parent::Py)\n\nA wrapper around a Python tensorstore.Transaction object. Used for atomic multi-write operations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.abort-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TransactionWrapper}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.abort","text":"abort(txn::TransactionWrapper)\n\nAbort the transaction, discarding any changes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.commit_async-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TransactionWrapper}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.commit_async","text":"commit_async(txn::TransactionWrapper) -> FutureWrapper{ReturnsNothing}\n\nStart committing the transaction asynchronously.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.commit_sync-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TransactionWrapper}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.commit_sync","text":"commit_sync(txn::TransactionWrapper)\n\nCommit the transaction synchronously and wait for completion.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.label-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TensorStoreWrapper, Vararg{Any}}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.label","text":"label(w::TensorStoreWrapper, labels...) -> TensorStoreWrapper\n\nAssign new labels to the dimensions of the TensorStore.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.labels-Tuple{PyTensorStore.IndexDomainWrapper}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.labels","text":"labels(w::IndexDomainWrapper) -> Vector{String}\n\nReturn the labels of the dimensions in the index domain.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.open-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.open","text":"open(spec; kwargs...) -> FutureWrapper{TensorStoreWrapper}\n\nOpen a TensorStore from a configuration dictionary or Spec. Returns a FutureWrapper that resolves to a TensorStoreWrapper.\n\nCommon keyword arguments:\n\ntransaction: A TransactionWrapper to use for this open operation.\ncreate: Boolean, whether to create the store if it doesn't exist.\nopen: Boolean, whether to open an existing store.\ndelete_existing: Boolean, whether to delete an existing store.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.result-Union{Tuple{Result}, Tuple{PyTensorStore.FutureWrapper{Result}, Vararg{Any}}} where Result","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.result","text":"result(w::FutureWrapper{Result}) -> Result\n\nWait for the future to complete and return the result, converted to the Julia type Result.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.transaction-Tuple{Function}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.transaction","text":"transaction(f::Function)\n\nRun a function f(txn) within a transaction.  The transaction is automatically committed if f returns normally,  and aborted if an exception is thrown.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.transaction-Tuple{}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.transaction","text":"transaction() -> TransactionWrapper\n\nCreate a new TensorStore transaction.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.translate_by-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TensorStoreWrapper, Vararg{Any}}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.translate_by","text":"translate_by(w::TensorStoreWrapper, offsets...) -> TensorStoreWrapper\n\nShift the coordinate system of the TensorStore by the given relative offsets. Offsets are relative to the current coordinate system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"reference/#PyTensorStore.translate_to-Tuple{PyTensorStore.TensorStoreWrapper, Vararg{Any}}","page":"API Reference","title":"PyTensorStore.translate_to","text":"translate_to(w::TensorStoreWrapper, coords...) -> TensorStoreWrapper\n\nShift the coordinate system of the TensorStore so that its origin starts at the specified coordinates. Coordinates are 1-based Julia indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PyTensorStore","page":"Home","title":"PyTensorStore","text":"PyTensorStore.jl provides a Julia wrapper around the Google TensorStore Python API. TensorStore is a library for efficiently reading and writing large multi-dimensional arrays, supporting various storage backends like Zarr, N5, and Google Cloud Storage.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Contents","page":"Home","title":"Contents","text":"Pages = [\"index.md\", \"guide.md\", \"reference.md\"]\nDepth = 2","category":"section"},{"location":"#Key-Features","page":"Home","title":"Key Features","text":"Familiar Interface: Implements much of the Julia AbstractArray interface, including 1-based indexing, size, axes, and eltype.\nAsynchronous Support: Built on TensorStore's asynchronous core, allowing for non-blocking I/O.\nPowerful Indexing: Support for labeled indexing, coordinate translation, and complex domain transformations.\nTransactions: Support for atomic multi-write operations.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"PyTensorStore\")\n\nNote: This package requires a working Python installation with the tensorstore package. CondaPkg.jl is used to manage this dependency automatically.","category":"section"}]
